Sentinel Deep Space Mining Operations (SDSMO) was created and maintained by the Deep Space Surveying program of Sentinel Logistic Services. 
Observations can be tracked on ED Astro using this link: 
https://edastro.com/galmap/?custom=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SentinelLogistics-data/SDSMO/refs/heads/main/zones.json

About SDSMO
The purpose of the project is to map and maintain a list of potential mining operations, with focus on two types of operations; core mining and fuel mining. 

Zones 1, 2, and 3 were chosen at random. The "alpha" system represents the first mineable system in that grouping. 
A discovery scan was done on surrounding systems, followed by a FSS. Ringed planets had a surface scan done to find core types. A breakdown can be found in the "Sites" file.

Interstallar Fuel Sites (IFS) are not related to the zone scans done in the first grouping. IFS markers represent sites found during dedicated refuelling missions
while moving a carrier long distances. No other core data is maintained for these datapoints, only that the site contains tritium. 
